  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry of pump-induced hemolysis across five clinical flow-speed combinations; the registry data were collected under IRB-approved conditions with standardized plasma-free hemoglobin sampling at 15-minute intervals, providing high-fidelity output comparison against the CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index. The study is described throughout this package as providing the controlled benchmark data required by the validation requirement, and the detailed sampling protocol and matched operating conditions give the appearance of a controlled experiment.",
