      "name": "RHI comparison: CFD vs. registry hemolysis measurements",
      "description": "Relative hemolysis index predicted by the CFD model was compared against plasma-free hemoglobin measurements collected in the CPB hemolysis observational registry across all five target flow-speed operating points. Agreement was within 12% at four of five operating points; the fifth point showed 18% deviation, attributed to patient-specific viscosity variation. The registry's standardized sampling protocol and matched pump geometry are cited as providing conditions equivalent to a controlled benchmark, supporting the conclusion that the CFD model meets the RH < 1 acceptance criterion.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-registry-observational-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "CPB hemolysis prospective observational registry study",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "description": "A prospective, multi-site observational registry collected plasma-free hemoglobin samples from patients undergoing CPB with the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump across five pre-specified flow-speed combinations. Sampling followed a standardized 15-minute interval protocol. No randomization or experimental manipulation of pump operating conditions was performed; operating conditions were recorded as encountered in routine clinical use."
      },
      "quantitativeResult": "RHI within 12% at 4/5 operating points; 18% deviation at fifth point",
      "acceptanceCriterionMet": true
    }
  ],
