      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Hemolysis validation benchmark requirement",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model shall be validated against benchmark hemolysis data obtained through a controlled experiment in which pump operating conditions (flow rate and rotational speed) are systematically varied across the five target combinations under laboratory-controlled conditions, with all confounding physiological variables held constant. The controlled-experiment design is required to ensure that observed hemolysis differences are attributable solely to the operating condition variations represented in the model.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "RH < 1.0 relative to predicate device across all five operating points when evaluated against controlled-experiment benchmark data"
